<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
4.6.4. 
<taxonomicName LSID="http://zoobank.org/62453049-1FB6-44A9-BFE6-E41CD40B9515" authority="Djernæs &amp; Murienne, 2022" authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" status="subfam. nov." subFamily="Austrostylopyginae">Austrostylopyginae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="209">subfam. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="type-genus">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Type-genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mackerras, 1968.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
See 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mackerras’">Mackerras'</normalizedToken>
(1968a)
</bibRefCitation>
diagnosis for genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
In all our analyses, we found a highly supported clade (pp = 100, bs = 97-100) consisting of four species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
s.l.) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eppertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eppertia" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Eppertia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
). The four species were 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta shelfordi" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shelfordi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta shelfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Shaw), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. W23, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. W24 and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Princis" baseAuthorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eppertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eppertia aptera" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Eppertia aptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Princis). Our analyses generally placed this group as sister to all other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Blattidae</taxonomicName>
except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roth" authorityYear="2003" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Duchailluiinae">Duchailluiinae</taxonomicName>
, but some analyses of the complete data set placed the group as sister to 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
(Table S2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
The four species in the group belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">Mackerras (1968a)</bibRefCitation>
; all four species were identified by JM using 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">Mackerras (1968a)</bibRefCitation>
. Mackerras erected 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
) with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shaw" baseAuthorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta shelfordi" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shelfordi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta shelfordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the type species to accommodate six Australian and New Guinean species that she considered intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
. Mackerras stated that the general appearance is very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Platyzosteria" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyzosteria" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Platyzosteria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
), but that the legs (specifically the metatarsal spines, symmetry of the pretarsal claws and shape of the femoral comb) are more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
. Mackerras found that the proventriculus is blattine-like while the shape of the spermatheca and L2 in the male genitalia and the laterosternal shelf in the female genitalia is polyzosteriine-like. 
<bibRefCitation author="Princis, K" editor="Beier, M" journalOrPublisher="W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="1041 - 1224" refId="B70" refString="Princis, K, 1971. Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae. In: Beier, M, Ed., Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage: 1041 - 1224" title="Blattariae: Subordo Epilamproidea. Fam.: Ectobiidae." volumeTitle="Orthopterorum Catalogus, Pars 14." year="1971">Princis (1971)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but transferred 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. aptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">E. aptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Eppertia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eppertia" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Eppertia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Polyzosteriinae">Polyzosteriinae</taxonomicName>
) instead of including it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johns" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Celatoblatta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Celatoblatta" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Celatoblatta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as he did with the other members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="209">
Based on our results, we restore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">Mackerras (1968a)</bibRefCitation>
. However, our results do not support placing this genus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Blattinae">Blattinae</taxonomicName>
. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be firmly placed within any of the existing subfamilies, neither based on our molecular results nor based on 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" author="Mackerras, MJ" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" pagination="511 - 575" refId="B53" refString="Mackerras, MJ, 1968a. Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae. Australian Journal of Zoology 16 (3): 511 - 575, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" title="Australian Blattidae (Blattodea) IX. Revision of the Polyzosteriinae tribe Methanini, Tryonicinae, and Blattinae." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9680511" volume="16" year="1968 a">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mackerras’">Mackerras'</normalizedToken>
(1968a)
</bibRefCitation>
morphological observations. Hence, we place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mackerras" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Blattidae" genus="Austrostylopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Austrostylopyga" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="209">Austrostylopyga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a separate subfamily, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Djernæs &amp; Murienne" authorityYear="2022" family="Blattidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="209" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Austrostylopyginae">Austrostylopyginae</taxonomicName>
, which occurs in Australia and New Guinea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
